quizzes.question:
How many times will the following code print "Hello"?
$i = 1;
do {  echo "Hello"; }
while($i < 0);

quizzes.textContent:
[h1]The do...while Loop[/h1]

The[b] do...while[/b] loop will always execute the block of code once, check the condition, and repeat the loop as long as the specified condition is true.

[b]Syntax:[/b] [code format="php"][b]do [/b]{
  code to be executed;
} [b]while [/b](condition is [b]true[/b]); [/code]
[note]Regardless of whether the condition is [b]true [/b]or [b]false[/b], the code will be executed at least [b]once[/b], which could be needed in some situations.[/note]

[h1]The do...while Loop[/h1]

The example below will write some output, and then increment the variable $i by one. Then the condition is checked, and the loop continues to run, as long as $i is less than or equal to 7.[code format="php" codeId="479"]$i = 5;
do {
   echo "The number is " . $i . "<br/>";
   $i++;
} while($i <= 7);

//Output
//The number is 5
//The number is 6
//The number is 7[/code]
[note]Note that in a [b]do while[/b] loop, the condition is tested AFTER executing the statements within the loop. This means that the [b]do while[/b] loop would execute its statements at least once, even if the condition is false the first time.[/note]
